1. What specific data or records exist to confirm that the temperatures during the Montane Yukon Arctic Ultra have indeed reached as low as -50 degrees Celsius with wind chill?
2. Can you provide evidence from race reports, participant testimonials, or official sources that support the claim that the Montane Yukon Arctic Ultra is considered one of the toughest ultramarathons in the world?
3. Are there any rankings, comparisons, or expert assessments available that objectively evaluate the difficulty level of the Montane Yukon Arctic Ultra in relation to other ultramarathons worldwide?
